1
00:00:00,935 --> 00:00:02,735
<i> Previously on</i> Lucifer...

2
00:00:02,737 --> 00:00:04,937
LUCIFER:<i> Operation "Help Lucifer</i>
<i> Escape From the Hospital."</i>

3
00:00:04,939 --> 00:00:07,606
<i> And you, my dear doctor,</i>
<i> are going to help me. </i>
Let's go.

4
00:00:07,608 --> 00:00:09,008
LINDA:
<i> The three of you plan to use</i>

5
00:00:09,010 --> 00:00:11,276
this Flaming Sword

6
00:00:11,278 --> 00:00:13,679
to cut through the gates
of Heaven and go home.

7
00:00:13,681 --> 00:00:15,314
What does Maze think
of your plan?

8
00:00:15,316 --> 00:00:16,582
Well, I don't know;
I haven't told her.

9
00:00:16,584 --> 00:00:18,917
So what, are you
going on a vacation?

10
00:00:18,919 --> 00:00:20,486
Lucifer didn't tell you.

11
00:00:20,488 --> 00:00:22,554
We're all going
back to Heaven.

12
00:00:22,556 --> 00:00:24,089
LUCIFER:<i> She's been acting</i>
<i> very odd recently,</i>

13
00:00:24,091 --> 00:00:26,091
on edge.

14
00:00:26,093 --> 00:00:27,359
<i> This obsession</i>
<i> with getting home</i>

15
00:00:27,361 --> 00:00:29,795
<i> is a bit much,</i>
<i> don't you think?</i>

16
00:00:29,797 --> 00:00:34,633
MOM:<i> That's because only you,</i>
<i>my Lightbringer, can ignite it.</i>

17
00:00:34,635 --> 00:00:36,268
That's it?
It's all I've got!

18
00:00:36,270 --> 00:00:37,536
You have to try harder.

19
00:00:37,538 --> 00:00:40,172
I'm not broken;
the sword must be.

20
00:00:40,174 --> 00:00:42,307
<i> This is what Uriel</i>
<i> was trying to tell me.</i>

21
00:00:42,309 --> 00:00:43,709
There's another piece missing.

22
00:00:46,847 --> 00:00:49,048
♪ ♪

23
00:00:54,588 --> 00:00:58,090
♪ I saw you walking on
the runway ♪

24
00:00:58,092 --> 00:01:01,393
♪ While I was walking
with my baby ♪

25
00:01:01,395 --> 00:01:05,664
♪ Thinking that the people
of this town are all... ♪

26
00:01:05,666 --> 00:01:07,633
Lucifer, we need
to talk about something.

27
00:01:07,635 --> 00:01:10,702
What-- Can it wait?
I'm busy keeping an eye

28
00:01:10,704 --> 00:01:12,237
on our mercurial mother.

29
00:01:12,239 --> 00:01:15,374
No, it's important.
I think you might be in danger.

30
00:01:17,011 --> 00:01:18,677
Is it the Yakuza?

31
00:01:18,679 --> 00:01:20,012
The Nephilim?

32
00:01:20,014 --> 00:01:21,547
One Million Mums?

33
00:01:21,549 --> 00:01:22,514
It's Maze.

34
00:01:22,516 --> 00:01:24,349
She's angry with you, brother.

35
00:01:24,351 --> 00:01:27,352
(laughs) Well, is it
Tuesday already?

36
00:01:27,354 --> 00:01:29,054
Anger is Maze's
default setting,

37
00:01:29,056 --> 00:01:31,290
sort of baked into
her demon DNA.

38
00:01:31,292 --> 00:01:33,659
No, this is
different, Luci.

39
00:01:33,661 --> 00:01:35,661
I think you really need
to talk to her.

40
00:01:35,663 --> 00:01:37,362
She'll get over it;
she always does.

41
00:01:37,364 --> 00:01:39,364
Right now, we have bigger
issues to deal with,

42
00:01:39,366 --> 00:01:42,501
like whether or not
Mum is wasting our time.

43
00:01:43,971 --> 00:01:45,370
If she believes her client

44
00:01:45,372 --> 00:01:48,407
has found another piece
of the Flaming Sword, so do I.

45
00:01:48,409 --> 00:01:51,610
Oh, such a loyal son.

46
00:01:51,612 --> 00:01:53,479
But Mum hasn't
adapted to this world

47
00:01:53,481 --> 00:01:55,514
as well as you
might think.

48
00:01:55,516 --> 00:01:58,350
This chap could be conning her.

49
00:01:58,352 --> 00:02:00,119
I think I'm gonna
go make sure...

50
00:02:00,121 --> 00:02:03,188
She seems
to be doing just fine.

51
00:02:05,192 --> 00:02:06,959
That's not the money, is it?

52
00:02:06,961 --> 00:02:09,461
Of course not. She wouldn't
bring it to the meeting.

53
00:02:11,098 --> 00:02:12,264
Oh, no. Of course not.

54
00:02:12,266 --> 00:02:13,632
I mean, that would be
absurd, wouldn't it?

55
00:02:13,634 --> 00:02:15,667
She's just showing it to him.
I mean, it's not like

56
00:02:15,669 --> 00:02:17,769
she's gonna hand it to him
before she...

57
00:02:17,771 --> 00:02:18,871
gets the piece.

58
00:02:18,873 --> 00:02:20,506
That's great.

59
00:02:20,508 --> 00:02:24,309
And now she's letting
him leave. Marvelous.

60
00:02:28,816 --> 00:02:29,882
Well, that went well.

61
00:02:29,884 --> 00:02:30,883
LUCIFER:
Oh, you think so,

62
00:02:30,885 --> 00:02:33,219
do you?
I do.

63
00:02:33,220 --> 00:02:35,554
He has what we need in his safe
in the back room.

64
00:02:35,556 --> 00:02:36,388
Oh.

65
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:37,789
He's going to get it right now.

66
00:02:37,791 --> 00:02:40,425
Mum, you just handed him
a briefcase full of cash

67
00:02:40,427 --> 00:02:42,427
with no proof whatsoever
he has what we need.

68
00:02:42,429 --> 00:02:44,696
And?
You've been conned.

69
00:02:44,698 --> 00:02:47,032
(scoffs) He's a client
of mine, darling.

70
00:02:47,034 --> 00:02:48,133
I don't think

71
00:02:48,135 --> 00:02:50,235
he'd be that foolhardy.
Oh.

72
00:02:52,573 --> 00:02:55,274
Well, I'm sure
he'll be right back.

73
00:02:57,244 --> 00:02:59,411
Maybe we should go check
just to be sure.

74
00:02:59,413 --> 00:03:01,380
I think that's a good idea,
don't you?

75
00:03:02,183 --> 00:03:03,649
Oh.

76
00:03:08,155 --> 00:03:10,789
Huh. See?
He didn't con me.

77
00:03:10,791 --> 00:03:13,492
Look, instead he's dead,
and someone robbed him

78
00:03:13,494 --> 00:03:15,727
of what's ours--
much better.

79
00:03:15,729 --> 00:03:19,398
Well, the good news is,
after this spectacular bungling,

80
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:22,067
I happen to work with
a homicide detective.

81
00:03:22,069 --> 00:03:23,636
If you find the killer,

82
00:03:23,637 --> 00:03:25,204
then you'll find our piece
of the Flaming Sword.

83
00:03:25,206 --> 00:03:26,405
Hey, but, Mom...

84
00:03:26,407 --> 00:03:27,973
The challenge is making sure
we catch the case

85
00:03:27,975 --> 00:03:29,491
before some other detective.

86
00:03:29,492 --> 00:03:31,008
But what about...
I may be able to help.

87
00:03:31,011 --> 00:03:33,679
Really?
I'm all ears.

88
00:03:33,681 --> 00:03:35,681
(door closes)

89
00:03:43,557 --> 00:03:45,224
Is everything all right here?

90
00:03:45,226 --> 00:03:46,692
Yeah, everything's fine, Maze.

91
00:03:46,694 --> 00:03:49,828
You can, uh, you-you can
put away the knives.

92
00:03:51,799 --> 00:03:54,633
We'll be in touch,
Dr. Martin.

93
00:03:57,805 --> 00:03:59,838
Excuse me.

94
00:04:00,975 --> 00:04:03,709
Uh, Maze.

95
00:04:03,711 --> 00:04:05,944
Maze.

96
00:04:05,946 --> 00:04:07,479
Oh, my Lord.

97
00:04:08,549 --> 00:04:10,649
Who the hell was that?

98
00:04:10,651 --> 00:04:15,053
<i> That</i> was the chairman
of the ethics review board.

99
00:04:15,055 --> 00:04:16,054
Are you okay?

100
00:04:16,056 --> 00:04:18,023
No.

101
00:04:18,025 --> 00:04:20,659
No, I am not.

102
00:04:20,661 --> 00:04:22,261
No, Maze. No, no,
no, don't, don't.

103
00:04:22,263 --> 00:04:23,762
That won't do any good.

104
00:04:23,764 --> 00:04:25,230
What happened?

105
00:04:25,232 --> 00:04:26,498
A couple of weeks ago,

106
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:28,533
I maybe, sort of...

107
00:04:28,535 --> 00:04:31,870
helped Lucifer break out
of a mental institution.

108
00:04:31,872 --> 00:04:34,172
Using my own name.

109
00:04:34,174 --> 00:04:36,074
It's my fault, really.

110
00:04:36,076 --> 00:04:38,610
No, it is not your fault.
It is Lucifer's fault.

111
00:04:38,612 --> 00:04:40,579
It's always
Lucifer's fault.

112
00:04:40,581 --> 00:04:43,282
First, I find out he's
ditching me to go to Heaven,

113
00:04:43,284 --> 00:04:45,317
and now he's hurting you.

114
00:04:45,319 --> 00:04:48,120
Look, I'm gonna fix this, Linda.

115
00:04:48,122 --> 00:04:51,590
And then him and I are gonna
have a little talk.

116
00:04:51,592 --> 00:04:53,392
♪ ♪

117
00:04:53,394 --> 00:04:57,629
♪ Trying to please everybody ♪

118
00:04:57,631 --> 00:05:02,734
♪ You just let everyone down ♪

119
00:05:02,736 --> 00:05:05,370
♪ One, two... one, two, three. ♪

120
00:05:10,444 --> 00:05:12,644
Hey, I should get my own desk.
Not happening.

121
00:05:12,646 --> 00:05:14,479
Right next to yours
would probably be best.

122
00:05:14,481 --> 00:05:15,681
Definitely not happening.

123
00:05:16,550 --> 00:05:17,949
Why are you hovering over me?

124
00:05:17,951 --> 00:05:19,468
I'm not hovering.

125
00:05:19,469 --> 00:05:20,986
I'm just spending
time with my partner.

126
00:05:20,988 --> 00:05:23,622
Oh, well, since you're here,

127
00:05:23,624 --> 00:05:26,325
why don't you help me
with this paperwork.

128
00:05:26,327 --> 00:05:28,427
I could really get
used to this, partner.

129
00:05:28,429 --> 00:05:29,528
Right. Yes, on
second thought,

130
00:05:29,530 --> 00:05:31,096
maybe a desk in the
far corner might...

131
00:05:31,098 --> 00:05:32,097
Mm-mm.

132
00:05:32,099 --> 00:05:33,465
Oh! Ms. Richards.

133
00:05:33,467 --> 00:05:37,302
Detective Decker. Just the woman
I was hoping to see.

134
00:05:37,304 --> 00:05:39,504
Well, I feel the opposite.
If you'll excuse me.

135
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:40,706
Hear me out.

136
00:05:40,708 --> 00:05:42,274
A client of
mine called.

137
00:05:42,276 --> 00:05:43,909
He sounded very worried.

138
00:05:43,911 --> 00:05:46,144
I think he might be
in terrible danger.

139
00:05:46,146 --> 00:05:47,412
Oh, that's awful.

140
00:05:47,414 --> 00:05:48,747
Detective, we should
do something.

141
00:05:48,749 --> 00:05:50,182
He's at a bar downtown.

142
00:05:50,184 --> 00:05:53,085
Would you come with me
and make sure that he's okay?

143
00:05:53,087 --> 00:05:54,386
Nope.

144
00:05:54,388 --> 00:05:56,021
Nope?

145
00:05:56,023 --> 00:05:58,240
I'm a homicide cop.

146
00:05:58,241 --> 00:06:00,458
I do not go around
checking on worried criminals

147
00:06:00,461 --> 00:06:02,594
like a nanny, Charlotte.

148
00:06:02,596 --> 00:06:05,597
So if we're done here.
I heard... things.

149
00:06:07,701 --> 00:06:09,000
On a...

150
00:06:09,002 --> 00:06:11,269
On-on the phone call.

151
00:06:11,271 --> 00:06:12,471
Like?

152
00:06:14,308 --> 00:06:18,009
Fingers... pointing.

153
00:06:18,011 --> 00:06:19,211
You heard

154
00:06:19,213 --> 00:06:21,480
fingers pointing?

155
00:06:22,216 --> 00:06:23,782
Very angrily.

156
00:06:23,784 --> 00:06:24,850
Yes.

157
00:06:27,988 --> 00:06:29,121
Also, a gunshot.

158
00:06:29,123 --> 00:06:31,056
Sounded like he was...

159
00:06:31,058 --> 00:06:33,725
dying, or, um...

160
00:06:33,727 --> 00:06:35,127
melting?

161
00:06:36,397 --> 00:06:38,563
It's hard to tell.

162
00:06:38,565 --> 00:06:39,664
Charlotte...

163
00:06:39,666 --> 00:06:41,233
It sounds worth our time,
actually.

164
00:06:41,235 --> 00:06:42,601
Agreed.

165
00:06:42,603 --> 00:06:44,870
Why didn't you just
lead with that?

166
00:06:51,512 --> 00:06:53,011
The lock's damaged.

167
00:06:53,013 --> 00:06:54,179
LUCIFER:
Is it?

168
00:06:57,384 --> 00:06:59,418
CHLOE:
Looks like you're right.

169
00:06:59,420 --> 00:07:01,486
He's been dead
about an hour.

170
00:07:01,488 --> 00:07:03,588
Oh? Impressive guess,
Detective.

171
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:08,927
Uh, I'm assuming
from the... discoloration.

172
00:07:08,929 --> 00:07:11,329
Well, that wasn't
a complete Dumpster fire,

173
00:07:11,331 --> 00:07:13,732
but now that we're finished,
you can see yourself out.

174
00:07:13,734 --> 00:07:15,801
I'll do nothing of the sort.

175
00:07:15,803 --> 00:07:18,170
Fine. I'll show you out,
if you insist.

176
00:07:18,172 --> 00:07:19,971
I'm not going anywhere.

177
00:07:19,973 --> 00:07:23,341
But the detective and I have
got everything handled now.

178
00:07:23,343 --> 00:07:26,211
This is far too important
to leave to just the two of you.

179
00:07:26,213 --> 00:07:27,479
I will stick around.

180
00:07:27,481 --> 00:07:28,447
Mum.

181
00:07:28,449 --> 00:07:29,481
Besides,

182
00:07:29,483 --> 00:07:31,583
we'll get to work together.

183
00:07:31,585 --> 00:07:33,118
Won't that be fun?

184
00:07:35,489 --> 00:07:37,689
♪ ♪

185
00:07:44,598 --> 00:07:46,364
ELLA: We're running tests for
gunshot residue and cocaine.

186
00:07:46,366 --> 00:07:47,799
Should have those
in, like, five minutes.

187
00:07:47,801 --> 00:07:49,334
Okay. Good.

188
00:07:49,336 --> 00:07:51,336
(siren wailing in distance)

189
00:07:51,338 --> 00:07:53,004
Oh, Charlotte.

190
00:07:53,006 --> 00:07:54,673
You're still here, huh?
Well, he was my client.

191
00:07:54,675 --> 00:07:57,442
I thought I might be
of help to the case.

192
00:07:57,444 --> 00:07:59,578
But if not, we could always
get her to shoo along

193
00:07:59,580 --> 00:08:01,246
and we can carry on
with our business.

194
00:08:01,248 --> 00:08:02,314
No. I'm sure she could be
very helpful.

195
00:08:02,316 --> 00:08:04,483
So tell me,
why does Zeke Moore,

196
00:08:04,485 --> 00:08:06,351
a manager at
an import/export company,

197
00:08:06,353 --> 00:08:07,719
have you representing him?

198
00:08:07,721 --> 00:08:09,888
Because I'm the best.
At getting criminals off.

199
00:08:09,890 --> 00:08:11,223
Well, that's not true.

200
00:08:11,225 --> 00:08:13,258
I haven't slept with
any of my clients.

201
00:08:13,260 --> 00:08:14,259
What?

202
00:08:14,261 --> 00:08:15,360
(sighs)
You represent

203
00:08:15,362 --> 00:08:16,428
the worst of the worst.

204
00:08:16,430 --> 00:08:17,629
So why was Zeke a client?

205
00:08:17,631 --> 00:08:20,165
Because he works
for Bianca Ruiz.

206
00:08:20,167 --> 00:08:21,333
What? The tequila magnate?

207
00:08:21,335 --> 00:08:23,068
Bianca's tequila empire
is a front.

208
00:08:23,070 --> 00:08:26,338
She uses the distribution routes
to sell guns, drugs,

209
00:08:26,340 --> 00:08:28,473
and, oh, yeah, people.

210
00:08:28,475 --> 00:08:31,176
So we've been after her
for a long time.

211
00:08:31,178 --> 00:08:32,577
Who do you think did this?

212
00:08:32,579 --> 00:08:34,579
A rival of some sort?

213
00:08:34,581 --> 00:08:36,448
CHLOE: Well, that's actually
a good question.

214
00:08:36,450 --> 00:08:38,283
Ella, what do we have?

215
00:08:38,285 --> 00:08:39,618
ELLA:
Well, no smoking gun,

216
00:08:39,620 --> 00:08:42,320
but poor Zeke here
got shot twice.

217
00:08:42,322 --> 00:08:43,622
First in the thigh--

218
00:08:43,624 --> 00:08:46,391
bullet winged him--
and then another

219
00:08:46,393 --> 00:08:50,328
went through his hand
hitting him in the chest.

220
00:08:50,330 --> 00:08:52,464
Probably trying
to defend himself.

221
00:08:52,466 --> 00:08:54,366
Too bad you can't catch bullets.

222
00:08:54,368 --> 00:08:55,567
Well, he can't maybe.

223
00:08:55,569 --> 00:08:57,435
I don't think this was
a professional hit.

224
00:08:57,437 --> 00:08:59,037
Maybe a robbery gone wrong.

225
00:08:59,039 --> 00:09:01,473
And idea of
what was taken?

226
00:09:01,475 --> 00:09:03,675
ELLA: Well, trace elements
point to cash,

227
00:09:03,677 --> 00:09:07,112
cocaine, gunpowder residue,
indicating weapons--

228
00:09:07,114 --> 00:09:09,581
all your basic bad guy stuff.

229
00:09:09,583 --> 00:09:11,182
No sign of forced entry, though.

230
00:09:11,184 --> 00:09:13,118
CHLOE: Which means the killer
either knew the combination,

231
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:15,954
or he just waited for the vic
to open it to strike.

232
00:09:15,956 --> 00:09:16,955
ELLA:
Mm-hmm.

233
00:09:16,957 --> 00:09:20,792
Hey, I got something here.

234
00:09:22,262 --> 00:09:23,828
Cell phone.

235
00:09:23,830 --> 00:09:27,332
No dust on it,
so it hasn't been there long.

236
00:09:27,334 --> 00:09:28,900
Well, Zeke had his phone on him,

237
00:09:28,902 --> 00:09:30,602
so this one could be
the killer's.

238
00:09:30,604 --> 00:09:32,604
Maybe he dropped it
during the fight

239
00:09:32,606 --> 00:09:35,240
or just didn't have time
to retrieve it.

240
00:09:35,242 --> 00:09:36,775
Passcode protected,

241
00:09:36,777 --> 00:09:38,443
of course.

242
00:09:38,445 --> 00:09:41,947
But the home screen is...
two eyes?

243
00:09:41,949 --> 00:09:43,682
Human female breasts.

244
00:09:43,683 --> 00:09:45,416
No. That is a woman's
perfectly freckled rump.

245
00:09:45,419 --> 00:09:47,719
CHLOE: So our lead
on the killer

246
00:09:47,721 --> 00:09:51,957
is a pair of butt-boob-eyes.

247
00:09:51,959 --> 00:09:53,959
It's a great start.

248
00:09:53,961 --> 00:09:55,427
♪ ♪

249
00:09:55,429 --> 00:09:57,629
♪ You caught a break ♪

250
00:09:57,631 --> 00:09:59,698
♪ When I gave you the time ♪

251
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:03,034
♪ Tell us now, little man,
what's what ♪

252
00:10:03,036 --> 00:10:06,171
♪ You're the one that had to go
show his stuff ♪

253
00:10:06,173 --> 00:10:09,407
♪ Oh, you're the one
that brought a shotgun... ♪

254
00:10:09,409 --> 00:10:10,942
Hello, Daniel.

255
00:10:10,944 --> 00:10:13,178
What are you doing here?

256
00:10:13,180 --> 00:10:16,681
