00:31:39,765 --> 00:31:41,765
Thanks.

779
00:31:41,767 --> 00:31:44,968
See? Light.

780
00:31:46,572 --> 00:31:48,572
(chuckles)

781
00:31:51,911 --> 00:31:53,510
Start talking.

782
00:31:55,848 --> 00:31:57,281
(sighs)

783
00:31:58,984 --> 00:32:01,184
<i> (piano playing dark melody)</i>

784
00:32:07,726 --> 00:32:10,193
(elevator bell dings)

785
00:32:10,195 --> 00:32:11,395
Ah!

786
00:32:11,397 --> 00:32:15,132
(plays Britney Spears'
"Oops!... I Did it Again")

787
00:32:15,134 --> 00:32:16,533
What happened to you?

788
00:32:16,535 --> 00:32:20,037
Oh, this. It's just a little
fisticuffs between friends.

789
00:32:20,039 --> 00:32:22,606
I just had
a very enlightening conversation

790
00:32:22,608 --> 00:32:23,707
with Charlotte Richards.

791
00:32:23,709 --> 00:32:25,208
Ah. Well, I've had my fill

792
00:32:25,210 --> 00:32:27,344
of enlightening conversations
for today, thank you.

793
00:32:27,346 --> 00:32:30,981
Lucifer, she told me
who she really is,

794
00:32:30,983 --> 00:32:32,683
and how you two are related.

795
00:32:32,685 --> 00:32:35,686
I somehow doubt that.

796
00:32:35,688 --> 00:32:37,254
It all makes sense.

797
00:32:37,256 --> 00:32:38,689
Why you were so disgusted

798
00:32:38,691 --> 00:32:41,124
when I suggested you two
had slept together.

799
00:32:41,126 --> 00:32:43,093
Why you act so weird
around her in general.

800
00:32:43,095 --> 00:32:45,162
She... really told you.

801
00:32:45,164 --> 00:32:46,563
What did she tell you?

802
00:32:46,565 --> 00:32:49,333
That she's your father's ex.

803
00:32:51,503 --> 00:32:53,804
Right, yes, no.
That's-that's true.

804
00:32:53,806 --> 00:32:54,972
Right, yeah.

805
00:32:54,974 --> 00:32:57,007
I mean, the way
she talked about your dad

806
00:32:57,009 --> 00:32:58,608
and-and what he put her through.

807
00:32:58,610 --> 00:33:02,012
Mm-hmm. Betrayal,
torture, Hell, et cetera.

808
00:33:02,014 --> 00:33:03,280
All true.
Mm-hmm.

809
00:33:03,282 --> 00:33:07,084
I just cannot imagine raising
kids with someone like that.

810
00:33:07,086 --> 00:33:08,885
Sympathy for the
goddess, Detective?

811
00:33:08,887 --> 00:33:10,320
(sighs)

812
00:33:10,322 --> 00:33:12,556
Why didn't you just tell me
she was your stepmom?

813
00:33:12,558 --> 00:33:17,227
Well, it didn't seem
that simple to explain.

814
00:33:17,229 --> 00:33:18,996
I mean, how did this
all come about, anyway?

815
00:33:18,998 --> 00:33:20,998
Well... (sighs)

816
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:23,700
I... I caught Charlotte
trying to steal evidence

817
00:33:23,702 --> 00:33:25,736
for Bianca Ruiz.

818
00:33:25,738 --> 00:33:26,970
What?

819
00:33:26,972 --> 00:33:28,271
Why would she do that?

820
00:33:28,273 --> 00:33:29,706
Well, apparently
Bianca figured out

821
00:33:29,708 --> 00:33:31,708
that Charlotte and I were
working together at the sting.

822
00:33:31,710 --> 00:33:33,210
Bianca threatened
Charlotte's family.

823
00:33:33,212 --> 00:33:35,112
I mean, she threatened you
if she didn't help.

824
00:33:35,114 --> 00:33:38,815
Well, that sounds plausible,
yes.

825
00:33:38,817 --> 00:33:40,650
I don't know.

826
00:33:40,652 --> 00:33:42,319
Something about it
doesn't feel right.

827
00:33:42,321 --> 00:33:45,055
I don't know if
I can trust her.

828
00:33:45,057 --> 00:33:46,523
Well, I mean, I know I'm biased,

829
00:33:46,525 --> 00:33:48,525
but one thing's for certain,
Detective:

830
00:33:48,527 --> 00:33:50,594
Charlotte Richards
will stop at nothing

831
00:33:50,596 --> 00:33:52,095
to protect her children.

832
00:33:53,499 --> 00:33:55,732
You can trust that.

833
00:33:55,734 --> 00:33:57,134
Hmm.

834
00:33:57,136 --> 00:33:59,903
Did you bring me
what I asked for?

835
00:33:59,905 --> 00:34:01,371
Mm.

836
00:34:02,841 --> 00:34:05,042
As promised.

837
00:34:07,179 --> 00:34:08,879
Make sure it's real.

838
00:34:08,881 --> 00:34:10,814
That it wasn't cloned.

839
00:34:18,624 --> 00:34:20,624
(liquid pouring)

840
00:34:25,731 --> 00:34:28,799
To the things a mother will do
for her children.

841
00:34:28,801 --> 00:34:32,135
I'll drink to that.

842
00:34:32,137 --> 00:34:33,670
BIANCA:
I can't even count the times

843
00:34:33,672 --> 00:34:34,738
that Chet has come close

844
00:34:34,740 --> 00:34:36,406
to destroying everything
I've built.

845
00:34:36,408 --> 00:34:39,209
MOM: Children always find
new ways to test us.

846
00:34:39,211 --> 00:34:41,144
She's talking
about Amenadiel.

847
00:34:41,146 --> 00:34:43,080
MOM:
Put us through... hell.

848
00:34:43,082 --> 00:34:44,414
That one's me.

849
00:34:44,416 --> 00:34:46,316
BIANCA:
And yet we still protect them.

850
00:34:46,318 --> 00:34:47,717
MOM:
Always.

851
00:34:50,189 --> 00:34:52,456
(computer trilling)

852
00:34:58,263 --> 00:35:00,430
Now for your side
of the bargain.

853
00:35:00,432 --> 00:35:02,132
(gasps)

854
00:35:02,134 --> 00:35:04,801
(clears throat)

855
00:35:04,803 --> 00:35:07,637
(static crackling)

856
00:35:07,639 --> 00:35:09,239
We lost the feed.

857
00:35:09,241 --> 00:35:10,574
She's up to something.
Well, no, no, no.

858
00:35:10,576 --> 00:35:11,875
She may have just
shorted the bug.

859
00:35:11,877 --> 00:35:13,443
No. Charlotte Richards
is either screwing us over

860
00:35:13,445 --> 00:35:14,911
or she's in trouble.

861
00:35:14,913 --> 00:35:16,146
Guys, get ready to go in.

862
00:35:16,148 --> 00:35:18,348
And she better
be in trouble.

863
00:35:21,220 --> 00:35:24,387
This opens a
safety deposit box.

864
00:35:24,389 --> 00:35:26,490
Inside you'll find what Zeke
was smuggling for you.

865
00:35:26,492 --> 00:35:28,558
This isn't what we agreed to.

866
00:35:28,560 --> 00:35:31,361
How do I know you'll hold up
your end of the deal?

867
00:35:31,363 --> 00:35:33,396
Because I always do.

868
00:35:33,398 --> 00:35:34,831
And quite honestly,
I don't see why

869
00:35:34,833 --> 00:35:36,900
you put so much value in...
(door opens)

870
00:35:36,902 --> 00:35:38,335
Freeze!
See your hands!

871
00:35:39,571 --> 00:35:43,039
LAPD. Bianca Ruiz,
you're under arrest.

872
00:35:43,041 --> 00:35:44,774
This is absurd.

873
00:35:44,776 --> 00:35:47,244
Charlotte. Charlotte.

874
00:35:47,246 --> 00:35:49,846
Will no longer be
representing you.

875
00:35:49,848 --> 00:35:53,383
You're making
a terrible mistake.

876
00:35:55,187 --> 00:35:56,319
Don't touch me.

877
00:35:56,321 --> 00:35:59,222
Charlotte, are you okay?

878
00:35:59,224 --> 00:36:00,357
Yes.
Lucifer, don't.

879
00:36:00,359 --> 00:36:01,758
Step away.
I need to search her.

880
00:36:01,760 --> 00:36:04,027
Well, I don't think
that's necessary, Detective.

881
00:36:04,029 --> 00:36:07,130
Well, I do.
It's okay, son.

882
00:36:07,132 --> 00:36:08,465
Fine.

883
00:36:08,467 --> 00:36:09,866
Arms out.

884
00:36:12,671 --> 00:36:14,204
Hmm.

885
00:36:15,440 --> 00:36:18,842
Oh, you're being
incredibly thorough.

886
00:36:18,844 --> 00:36:20,844
I like it.

887
00:36:20,846 --> 00:36:22,746
(clears throat)

888
00:36:22,748 --> 00:36:24,881
She's clean.
Well, I told you, Detective,

889
00:36:24,883 --> 00:36:26,583
she's got nothing to hide.

890
00:36:26,585 --> 00:36:28,385
MAN: The phone
was still unlocked.

891
00:36:28,387 --> 00:36:29,853
We have everything.

892
00:36:29,855 --> 00:36:32,189
Seems like we do.

893
00:36:33,992 --> 00:36:35,192
Let's, uh...

894
00:36:49,074 --> 00:36:50,874
A book?

895
00:36:50,876 --> 00:36:52,842
That's what Zeke smuggled
for me?

896
00:36:54,146 --> 00:36:56,680
Is this a joke?

897
00:36:56,682 --> 00:36:58,615
Well, if it were, I would have
chosen something funnier,

898
00:36:58,617 --> 00:37:00,817
like Douglas Adams or Freud.

899
00:37:00,819 --> 00:37:03,486
Are you certain that this is
all that was in

900
00:37:03,488 --> 00:37:05,455
the safety deposit box?
(sighs)

901
00:37:05,457 --> 00:37:08,124
Well, how is a book supposed
to ignite the sword?

902
00:37:08,126 --> 00:37:09,693
Maybe it's
an instruction manual.

903
00:37:11,663 --> 00:37:14,631
MOM: In an ancient language
I can't read.

904
00:37:14,633 --> 00:37:16,299
Wonderful.

905
00:37:16,301 --> 00:37:17,567
Here.

906
00:37:17,569 --> 00:37:19,202
Wh-- I can't read it.

907
00:37:19,204 --> 00:37:21,705
But you speak every language.

908
00:37:21,707 --> 00:37:23,240
Speak, not read.

909
00:37:23,241 --> 00:37:24,774
I've always found tongues
much more useful than books.

910
00:37:24,776 --> 00:37:26,142
So whatever
language this is...

911
00:37:26,144 --> 00:37:27,978
It's Sumerian.

912
00:37:27,980 --> 00:37:30,580
Unlike some of us who had
everything handed to him,

913
00:37:30,582 --> 00:37:34,284
I actually spent
my youth studying.

914
00:37:34,286 --> 00:37:36,019
(chuckles):
Excellent.

915
00:37:36,021 --> 00:37:38,788
My smart boy.

916
00:37:38,790 --> 00:37:42,125
How-how quickly
can you translate it?

917
00:37:42,127 --> 00:37:44,461
Um, should only
take me a few days.

918
00:37:44,463 --> 00:37:46,129
(chuckles)
Days?

919
00:37:46,131 --> 00:37:47,797
I don't have that kind of time.

920
00:37:47,799 --> 00:37:50,667
Mum, why have you got your
knickers in such a twist?

921
00:37:50,669 --> 00:37:53,069
Is there a reason why you're
in such a rush lately?

922
00:37:53,071 --> 00:37:56,273
I-I'm just anxious to see
the rest of the family.

923
00:37:57,209 --> 00:38:00,710
Please start translating.

924
00:38:04,249 --> 00:38:06,516
There's something
going on with her.

925
00:38:06,518 --> 00:38:10,654
Yeah. Or it's just that
time of the millennium.

926
00:38:12,758 --> 00:38:14,758
What?

927
00:38:22,834 --> 00:38:25,101
Excuse me.

928
00:38:25,103 --> 00:38:27,771
Not this time.

929
00:38:31,877 --> 00:38:32,876
(knocks)

930
00:38:32,878 --> 00:38:34,577
Hey.
Hey.

931
00:38:34,579 --> 00:38:36,579
Congrats on nabbing
Queen Tequila.

932
00:38:36,581 --> 00:38:39,316
Well, Chet's still out there,

933
00:38:39,318 --> 00:38:42,018
so this isn't over
until I find him.

934
00:38:42,020 --> 00:38:43,653
You and Charlotte Richards--

935
00:38:43,655 --> 00:38:45,989
that is the most awkward team-up
of the century.

936
00:38:45,991 --> 00:38:49,726
(chuckles) Actually, it wasn't
as bad as I expected.

937
00:38:49,728 --> 00:38:52,128
I learned a lot of
eye-opening things about her.

938
00:38:52,130 --> 00:38:54,764
That's for sure. Like her
being Lucifer's stepmom.

939
00:38:54,766 --> 00:38:56,533
Had no idea...
Wait a minute.

940
00:38:56,535 --> 00:38:59,035
She-- Stepmom?

941
00:38:59,037 --> 00:39:00,036
Yeah.

942
00:39:00,038 --> 00:39:01,438
Yes.

943
00:39:01,440 --> 00:39:05,408
That makes a weird amount
of sense, actually.

944
00:39:05,410 --> 00:39:07,911
Dan, I want you to be
careful with her.

945
00:39:07,913 --> 00:39:09,546
There's something about her
I don't trust.

946
00:39:09,548 --> 00:39:11,881
I'm gonna be fine, Chloe.

947
00:39:13,685 --> 00:39:15,485
Wait.
One more thing.
Yeah.

948
00:39:15,487 --> 00:39:18,388
If you married her,

949
00:39:18,390 --> 00:39:21,057
you'd kind of be
like Lucifer's dad.

950
00:39:21,059 --> 00:39:22,659
(laughs)

951
00:39:22,661 --> 00:39:24,561
Oh, my God.
Right?

952
00:39:24,563 --> 00:39:27,163
It's so, so messed up.

953
00:39:27,165 --> 00:39:30,066
♪ ♪

954
00:39:43,148 --> 00:39:45,515
I'm glad you agreed to meet me.

955
00:39:45,517 --> 00:39:47,450
Well, of course I did.

956
00:39:47,452 --> 00:39:50,553
I knew that book couldn't be it.

957
00:39:52,557 --> 00:39:53,823
Well, come on.

958
00:39:53,825 --> 00:39:57,093
Hand it over. I need
what Zeke really smuggled.

959
00:39:58,663 --> 00:39:59,796
Now.

960
00:40:04,503 --> 00:40:07,504
Mm. A knife.

961
00:40:07,506 --> 00:40:10,140
We already have...
(grunts)

962
00:40:10,142 --> 00:40:11,975
(gasping)

963
00:40:11,977 --> 00:40:14,744
My life is ruined!

964
00:40:14,746 --> 00:40:16,646
I don't want
to go to prison.

965
00:40:16,648 --> 00:40:18,114
This is all your fault!

966
00:40:18,116 --> 00:40:20,116
(panting)

967
00:40:21,086 --> 00:40:22,452
(groans)

968
00:40:30,695 --> 00:40:33,763
♪ You didn't plan a fight ♪

969
00:40:33,765 --> 00:40:34,697
(gasps)

970
00:40:34,699 --> 00:40:37,100
♪ Thought I was weak ♪

971
00:40:37,102 --> 00:40:40,870
(groans)
♪ But you underestimated me ♪

972
00:40:40,872 --> 00:40:42,572
(panting)
♪ Didn't you, baby? ♪

973
00:40:42,574 --> 00:40:43,873
(groans loudly)

974
00:40:43,875 --> 00:40:46,476
♪ If I'm bad, you're worse ♪

975
00:40:46,478 --> 00:40:49,245
♪ You cut and haunt me
like a curse ♪

976
00:40:49,247 --> 00:40:53,683
♪ You've got those
cruel intentions. ♪

977
00:40:53,685 --> 00:40:56,219
(playing gentle melody)

978
00:40:56,221 --> 00:40:59,722
Who knew translating could be
so exhausting. (chuckles)

979
00:41:01,526 --> 00:41:04,194
(sighs) Listen, I think
I found something.

980
00:41:04,196 --> 00:41:06,362
Huh?

981
00:41:06,364 --> 00:41:09,265
God shattered the Flaming Sword
into three distinct pieces.

982
00:41:09,267 --> 00:41:10,667
"The Blade of Death."

983
00:41:10,669 --> 00:41:12,035
LUCIFER:
Azrael's.

984
00:41:12,037 --> 00:41:13,870
AMENADIEL:
"The Medallion of Life."

985
00:41:13,872 --> 00:41:15,872
LUCIFER:
Johnson's belt buckle.

986
00:41:15,874 --> 00:41:19,542
And the key that binds them
all together.

987
00:41:21,780 --> 00:41:24,447
Well, keys don't bind,
they unlock.

988
00:41:24,449 --> 00:41:28,485
I think someone needs to go
back to translation school.

989
00:41:28,487 --> 00:41:30,787
(gentle melody continues)

990
00:41:30,789 --> 00:41:32,989
And guess who has the key.

991
00:41:36,428 --> 00:41:38,161
Well, don't leave me
in suspense.

992
00:41:38,163 --> 00:41:39,362
Who is it, brother?

993
00:41:39,364 --> 00:41:41,097
It says that God
entrusted the key

994
00:41:41,099 --> 00:41:43,967
to his favorite son.

995
00:41:43,969 --> 00:41:45,835
(sighs)

996
00:41:46,771 --> 00:41:49,606
Of course he gave it to you.

997
00:41:50,976 --> 00:41:52,442
It's always you, isn't it?

998
00:41:52,444 --> 00:41:53,710
Well, what are
you talking about?

999
00:41:53,712 --> 00:41:55,645
The only keys
I've got are these.

1000
00:41:55,647 --> 00:41:57,780
(plays notes)

1001
00:41:57,782 --> 00:42:00,283
What else did you bring
with you to Earth, Luci?

1002
00:42:00,285 --> 00:42:01,551
(chuckles softly)

1003
00:42:01,553 --> 00:42:03,953
Your ring.

1004
00:42:03,955 --> 00:42:06,122
I've never seen you without it;
maybe that's the key.

1005
00:42:06,124 --> 00:42:08,825
Well, the key to completing
my ensemble maybe.

1006
00:42:08,827 --> 00:42:10,026
Here.

1007
00:42:10,028 --> 00:42:12,662
Try and attach your ring
to this.

1008
00:42:12,664 --> 00:42:14,230
Brother.
Just do it.

1009
00:42:14,232 --> 00:42:16,065
And we'll confirm
what we already know.

1010
00:42:16,067 --> 00:42:18,167
Brother...
That Father's favorite,

1011
00:42:18,169 --> 00:42:19,602
despite everything
that you have done,

1012
00:42:19,604 --> 00:42:21,337
is and always has been you.

1013
00:42:21,339 --> 00:42:23,106
Look down.

1014
00:42:23,108 --> 00:42:24,307
(gasping)

1015
00:42:27,178 --> 00:42:29,479
LUCIFER:
Is that the key around your neck

1016
00:42:29,481 --> 00:42:31,748
or are you just
happy to see me?

1017
00:42:36,121 --> 00:42:39,556
He entrusted it...

1018
00:42:39,558 --> 00:42:42,125
to you, brother.

